FBIS3-4983 "dreas042_d_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 South Korea IAEA Inspection of DPRK Sites Begins 3 Mar OW0303135394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1339 GMT 3 Mar 94 OW0303135394 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vienna, March 3 KYODO -- A seven-member team began Thursday [3 March] inspecting North Korea's nuclear facilities, a spokesman for the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) said. The inspection of seven declared facilities will last through March 15, the spokesman said. The IAEA inspection team arrived in Pyongyang on Tuesday. The inspections followed an agreement reached by the United States and North Korea last Friday at a working-level meeting in New York that Pyongyang fully implement IAEA inspections of its seven declared nuclear plants.
